ABUJA – The Abia State Governor, Dr. Okezie Ikpeazu, has told one of his top aides, Enyinnaya Appolos, that he is doing well where he is receiving treatment after testing positive for Coronavirus Disease. Governor Ikpeazu was confirmed positive for COVID-19 over the weekend, with reports during the week having it that he had to be flown out of Abia State for further treatment in the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja. Appolos, who revealed his telephone conversation with the Governor on his Facebook page, however, did not mention Ikpeazu’s name. He said he spoke with Ikpeazu at about 5:18pm on Wednesday, with words of reassurance by the Governor that he was doing great. He wrote: “At exactly 5:18pm, Wednesday, 10th June, 2020, he said to me: ‘Nna, I’m very fine.  Very soon I will be back. I’m doing fine.’” (TheEagleonline) A private hospital in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Abuja, has rejected the Governor of Abia State, Okezie Ikpeazu (Ph.D), who sought treatment there for Coronavirus (COVID-19). The hospital, located in the Gudu area of the FCT, turned him down on the excuse “that they are into kidney transplant and… June 10, 2020 In "News" •Governor Okezie Ikpeazu ABUJA - Governor Okezie Ikpeazu of Abia State, who recently tested positive for Coronavirus (COVID-19), has been flown out of the state for further treatment, News Express learnt. Sources close to the Government House, Umuahia, said he was “flown to Abuja for treatment and was not in… June 9, 2020 In "News" UMUAHIA (Sundiata Post) - The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Abia North Senatorial District has expressed its support for the governor of Abia State, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu, describing the pro-Uche Ogah judgement of Justice Okon Abang of the Federal High Court in Abuja in as "controversial and contentious". A statement… July 15, 2016 In "Politics"